-- MOVES-FM Global names Thomas Lawson chief executive
-- 
-- Fri Jul 11, 2014 06:37AM EDT
-- None



July 11 (Reuters) - FM Global, a commercial and industrial property insurer, said Thomas Lawson will succeed Shivan Subramaniam as chief executive, effective Jan. 1, 2015.

Lawson, currently an executive vice president, joined the company in 1979. Subramaniam will retire on Dec. 31, after 40 years with the company, but will remain chairman of the board. The mutual insurance company also said Lawson was named president and elected to the board, effective Aug. 1, 2014. As president, Lawson will be responsible for the strategic and operational direction of the company. The company also appointed Jonathan Hall, another executive vice president, as chief operating officer from Aug. 1.